  CBS is thinking about creating original content for streaming video on demand services like Netflix, an executive told a group of investors today. Asked if he could see CBS producing a studio-caliber show along the lines of <a href="http://www.theverge.com/2013/2/12/3981996/house-of-cards-is-the-most-watched-thing-on-netflix-but-no-ones">Netflix's House of Cards</a>, Global Distribution Group CEO Armando Nu&ntilde;ez said, "it&rsquo;s definitely a possibility," adding, "we view Netflix, Amazon and all these SVOD platforms as new players. If you can get the right model to work, I can see us doing that." 
CBS was in early talks to resurrect 'Jericho' as a Netflix exclusive
Last year, reports surfaced that CBS was in early talks to <a href="http://www.tvguide.com/News/Exclusive-Netflix-Jericho-1046804.aspx" target="_blank">resurrect its popular action-drama, Jericho</a>, as a Netflix exclusive. The show developed a passionate following, but failed to get...
  
