  Ikea is making your dream of living in Ikea a reality. Inter Ikea Group, Ikea's parent company, is moving into urban development, and its first town is planned for south of Stratford, London. The half-billion dollar project isn't a new idea &mdash; planned communities and company towns already exist &mdash; but it's unclear what Ikea has to gain from the low-profit venture. The company is planning its town responsibly, with 15 percent of the apartments and family homes marked as affordably priced housing, and <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/magazine/173/ikea-urban-planning" target="_blank">Fast Company questions</a> whether the town is a convoluted tax haven or a somewhat philanthropic effort. Either way, the good news is that it should all come preassembled.
  
